      "coachingCues": [
        "Run FAST first — the move only works if you set up speed to change FROM",
        "Slow down like you're done running — make the defender think the play is over",
        "When you GO, lean forward and EXPLODE — be a rocket",
        "Freeze the defender's feet — when they slow down with you, that's when you blast past",
        "Arms tell the story — fast arms = fast, slow arms = slow, fast arms again = GONE"
      ],
      "commonMistakes": [
        "Not running fast enough before the hesitation (no speed contrast = no effect)",
        "Hesitating too long (gives defender time to recover and re-read you)",
        "Gradual slowdown instead of sudden (must be a sharp speed change)",
        "Not getting low on the burst (standing tall = slow acceleration)",
        "Looking at the defender during hesitation (look past them, not at them)"
      ]
    },
