      "coachingCues": [
        "Quick feet! Tap-tap-tap-tap like the ground is hot",
        "Don't go too wide — small, fast movements, not big lunges",
        "Keep your weight CENTERED during the shimmy — don't commit until you burst",
        "Watch the defender's hips — when they shift one way, you go the OTHER way",
        "The shimmy is the question, the burst is the answer"
      ],
      "commonMistakes": [
        "Shimmy steps too wide (takes too long to recover and burst)",
        "Committing weight during the shimmy (if you lean, you're stuck going that way)",
        "Too many shimmy steps (2-4 is enough — more than that and you're dancing, not playing)",
        "Shimmy without forward progress (you should still be moving slightly forward)",
